➡ Presence of pattern


  1. Calculate the auto-correlation coefficient (for 1999 lags)
  2. Use p-value to check pattern presence.
    Small pvalue suggests that the autocorrelation coefficient for that lag is significantly different from zero, indicating the presence of a pattern.
  • YES => data HAS a pattern (>80% lagged values)
  • NO => data DOES NOT have a pattern (>80% lagged values)
  • CHK => data MAY have a pattern (>20% lagged values show yes/no together)
